-- Motjoli Resources Plans an Iron Ore Mine in South Africa, MiningMX Reports
-- Antony Sguazzin
-- 2010-07-27T05:13:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/motjoli-resources-plans-an-iron-ore-mine-in-south-africa-miningmx-reports.html

          
          
             Motjoli Resources Ltd. is planning to
dig an 11 billion rand ($1.5 billion) iron ore mine near Piet
Retief in South Africa, MiningMX reported, without saying where
it got the information.  
 The mine could start production in 2012 and produce 20
million metric tons of ore a year, the Johannesburg-based
Internet news site said.   
